<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="NTM2.10">
<l>cītai vāyamuta muṇṭā yeṅkaḷ ciṟṟil nīcitai yēleṉṟu</l>
<l>vīti vāyviḷai yāṭu māyar ciṟumiyar maḻalaic collai</l>
<l>vēta vāyttoḻi lārkaḷ vāḻvilli puttūr maṉviṭṭu cittaṉṟaṉ</l>
<l>kōtai vāyttamiḻ valla varkuṟai viṉṟi vaikuntañ cērvarē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>Those who are capable [of mastering] the Tamil [that came] through the words of Kōtai</l>
<l rend="indent">[daughter] of Viṭṭucittaṉ, the king of Villiputtūr, where those whose words and</l>
<l rend="indent">profession are the Vedas</l>
<l>[who spoke] the lisping words of the cowherd girls who play in the street</l>
<l rend="indent">saying ‘O You who ate nectar from Sītā’s lips! Do not destroy our little</l>
<l rend="indent">[sand] house!’</l>
<l>will reach Vaikuntha without fail.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
</text>
